  "question_id": "63ea0bd4-8ce7-451a-b5bd-629b2b13b9a9",
  "short_text": "Double the Numbers",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a line of space-separated integers and doubles its value. The program should output the results as a space-separated sequence.\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nA single line of integers separated by spaces.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nA single line of doubled integers separated by spaces.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nIf the input is:\n\n```\n1 2 3 4\n```\n\nThe output should be:\n\n```\n2 4 6 8\n```",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "7b0aba67-15ea-4b1d-a0d7-f9a38c766655",
      "code_content": "def double_numbers(numbers):\n    return [num * 2 for num in numbers]\n\ninput_line = input().split()\nnumbers = [int(x) for x in input_line]\ndoubled_numbers = double_numbers(numbers)\n\n\nfor i in range(len(doubled_numbers)):\n    if i < len(doubled_numbers) - 1:\n        print(doubled_numbers[i], end=\" \")\n    else:\n        print(doubled_numbers[i])\n",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
